{
  "stem": "20609.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "You couldn't-- you weren't allowed to go to a museum, you weren't allowed to go to a-- to a play, you weren't allowed to go to a movie, you weren't allowed to go into a cafe house.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "My father occasionally years ago always took me with him once in a-- in a while so I could have a piece of cake and-- and my hot chocolate.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "All of a sudden, that was out, you know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And-- and then, of course, I imagine we didn't have the money anymore to-- to go to these places, even if we could.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So little by little, it was actually become impossible, much more for a kid, and it was for-- like you mentioned before, the Germans thought it was a great thing with the Nuremberg laws, the German Jews.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I-- I don't think if you had any-- that was the worst thing in the world.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "That should have been a signal for every Jew to get out of Europe or get out of Germany.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And at that time, that was possible.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "[DRINKS] My father opened up a store in 1937 again.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Now, that was stupid.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I-- I-- I told him that after the war.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I actually [INAUDIBLE] he was still alive.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "So-- so that's basically, I felt anti-Semitism all around.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I was very unhappy, I couldn't play, there was no places to go.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I used to love to go skating, ice skating.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "All of a sudden, you couldn't go there anymore.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And things like that, what kids like to do was all forbidden.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Passover was very beautiful, it was.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because many times, my-- my grandfather, and I got a picture of him, he used to come and visit us from Poland.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he conducted a service, he was a very religious person.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
